Diagnosis. Pronotum shorter than fore femur; disk without sharp lateral keels; lateral lobes nearly smooth, without wrinkles. Fore and middle tibiae dorsally with a subapical spine only on one side, exterior in fore tibiae and interior in middle ones. Median femur armed on posterior margin of ventral surface. Genicular lobes of hind femur unarmed on anterior margin. Female brachypterous or mesopterous. Ovipositor decurved. (from
Bey-Bienko, 1951
;
Liu, 2015
)

Included species.
Mongolodectes kiritshenkoi (
Miram, 1929
)
;
Mongolodectes alashanicus
Bey-Bienko, 1951
;
Mongolodectes kaszabi
Bazyluk, 1972
;
Mongolodectes huangxinleii
sp. nov.
